Golang implementation of popular tree command from linux.
Note: windows 10 has issue with ansi color, so for this release color output will be
--includestats Include File Stats in JSON Output
-o, --output string Put result in the output file (default "stdout")
-a, --all List all files & directories including hidden ones
-f, --fullpath Print full path prefix for all files
--noreport Omits printing of the file and directory report at the end of the tree listing.
-l, --followlink Follow link and list files in the link is for a directory
--prune Makes tree prune empty directories from the output
-L, --level int16 Max display depth of the directory tree (default -1)
--filelimit int Do not descend directories that contain more than # entries. (default -1)
--timefmt string Prints (implies -D) and formats the date according to the format string (default "Jan 2 15:04:05 PM")
-g, --group Print the group name, or GID
-D, --modtime Print the date of the last modification time for the file listed
-r, --reverse Sort the output in reverse alphabetic order
-t, --sortbymodtime Sort the output by last modification time instead of alphabetically
-P, --includepattern string List only those files which matches to wild-card pattern
-I, --excludepattern string Do not list those files that match the wild-card pattern.
